</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Compliance with Estyn’s standards is mandated by various legislations and regulations. Key legislative frameworks include:


























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-51_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Education Act 2005</strong> - Outlines Estyn's powers and duties, including its authority to inspect educational institutions and provide reports.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-54_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Learning and Skills Act 2000</strong> - Mandates the inspection of post-16 education and training, ensuring alignment with national standards.







</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-56_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Schools Standards and Organisation (Wales) Act 2013</strong> - This legislation focuses on improving school standards and gives Estyn the authority to conduct inspections and recommend improvements.








</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-58_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-59_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-60_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for implementation
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-62_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Institutions aiming to comply with Estyn’s standards should consider the following best practices:



























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-64_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-65_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular self-evaluation</strong> - Conducting regular self-evaluations helps institutions identify areas for improvement. Self-evaluation should be aligned with Estyn’s quality indicators, focusing on key aspects such as teaching quality, learner outcomes, and leadership effectiveness.







</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-67_ pf-text-1"><strong>Continuous Professional Development (CPD)</strong> - Investing in CPD for staff ensures that teaching practices remain current and effective. Regular training sessions, workshops, and courses can enhance educators' skills, directly impacting learner outcomes.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-69_ pf-text-1"><strong>Learner-centred approaches</strong> - Adopting learner-centred approaches ensures that educational practices meet the diverse needs of all learners. This involves personalised learning plans, active engagement strategies, and supportive learning environments.










</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-71_ pf-text-1"><strong>Effective leadership</strong> - Strong leadership is crucial for driving improvement. Leaders should focus on strategic planning, fostering a positive organisational culture, and ensuring that all staff are aligned with the institution’s goals and standards.











</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-73_ pf-text-1"><strong>Utilising technology</strong> - Leveraging technology can enhance teaching and learning experiences. Institutions should integrate digital tools and resources to support innovative teaching methods and improve learner engagement.












